org.jcvi.jillion.internal.trace.chromat.ztr.data

Enum DeltaEncodedData

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DeltaEncodedData>
      • org.jcvi.jillion.internal.trace.chromat.ztr.data.DeltaEncodedData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<DeltaEncodedData>, Data

    public enum DeltaEncodedData
extends Enum<DeltaEncodedData>
implements Data
    AbstractDeltaData is an abstract implementation of the Delta encoded Data formats. The Delta formats store the differences between successive bytes instead of the actual values. Different implementations of AbstractDeltaData are used for the different sizes of the encoded values.
    Author:
    dkatzel
    See Also:
    ZTR SPEC v1.2

      • getPaddingSize

        protected int getPaddingSize()
        Some implementations may have additional padding between the format byte and when the actual data starts. Usually this is to needed to make the total length of the data section divisible. Implementations may override this method to return a different padding size.
